# {{ project_name }} Architecture

{{ project_description }}

This document owns the repository-level architecture and invariants. Every
application and shared package owns an `ARCHITECTURE.md` scoped to its
directory; add one to another significant non-Skill directory when its
responsibilities, boundaries, data flows, or design decisions require more
detail. Under `.agents/skills/`, the collection `ARCHITECTURE.md` is the sole
architecture document: individual Skills own `SKILL.md` and purpose-specific
supporting references. Agent operating constraints are defined in `AGENTS.md`.

## Project structure

```text
.
├── .agents/
│   ├── .claude-plugin/
│   │   └── plugin.json         # Claude Code manifest; .agents is the plugin root
│   ├── .codex-plugin/
│   │   └── plugin.json         # Codex manifest; .agents is the plugin root
│   ├── plugins/
│   │   └── marketplace.json    # Empty Codex parent marketplace catalog
│   └── skills/                 # Canonical shared uv/pnpm member for Agent Skills
├── .claude/
│   ├── settings.json                # Claude Code project declaration of this marketplace
│   └── skills -> ../.agents/skills  # Claude Code development-time view of canonical skills
├── .claude-plugin/
│   └── marketplace.json        # Empty Claude Code parent marketplace catalog
├── apps/                       # uv/pnpm applications directly invoked by users, Agents, or automations
├── packages/                   # uv/pnpm language APIs consumed by distinct workspace members
├── repos/                      # Optional child Git submodules for parent repositories
│   └── .gitkeep                # Preserves the empty submodule placement directory
├── .gitmodules                 # Empty until Git records child submodule metadata
├── .gitignore                  # Local artifacts and credentials excluded from Git
├── AGENTS.md                   # Agent operating constraints
├── CLAUDE.md                   # Claude Code entry point for the same constraints
├── ARCHITECTURE.md             # Repository-level architecture
├── package.json                # Root pnpm workspace manifest
├── pyproject.toml              # Root uv workspace configuration
└── README.md                   # Project overview and onboarding
```

## Invariants

- Stable project knowledge belongs in tracked documentation or source files.
- Local execution state, credentials, and private evidence remain outside Git.
- Reusable deterministic logic belongs in a package or skill-owned script.
- `apps/` owns direct execution surfaces, including CLI, web, native, and
  automation entry points, together with their runtime and entry-point
  contracts.
- `packages/` owns only language-level APIs actually consumed by a distinct
  application or package; it does not own a direct user, Agent, or automation
  entry point.
- Unshared implementation remains in its owning application. Extract only the
  portion with an actual distinct consumer into `packages/`.
- An application is not a language-level workspace dependency. A member that
  needs another member's logic consumes an explicit package instead.
- Qualitative agent workflows are explicit, bounded, and self-describing.
- `.agents/skills/` is the only source of truth for skills; `.claude/skills`
  is a development-time relative link to it.
- `.agents/skills/ARCHITECTURE.md` is the sole architecture document in the
  Skills subtree. Individual Skills use `SKILL.md` and purpose-specific
  `references/` files rather than nested `ARCHITECTURE.md` files.
- `.agents/` is the plugin root. Its manifests reference `./skills/`, which is
  the physical skill directory in the Git subdirectory package.
- `.agents/plugins/marketplace.json` and `.claude-plugin/marketplace.json` are
  empty parent-marketplace placeholders. They do not discover submodules or
  install plugins; a parent explicitly adds each child plugin entry when it
  chooses to distribute it.
- `.claude/settings.json` declares this repository root as the Claude Code
  `directory` marketplace. Its empty `enabledPlugins` map records that no child
  plugin is selected until the parent adds an explicit
  `<plugin>@<marketplace>` entry.
- `repos/` contains only optional child Git submodules; `.gitkeep` preserves
  the placement directory before any child is added.
- `.gitmodules` remains empty until `git submodule add` records each child's
  required Git path and URL metadata.
- Parent marketplaces select `.agents/` through a pinned Git subdirectory
  source, independent of a parent repository's submodule checkout.
